1) In createXYZ.cpp change the dimensions of the box (Lx = Ly = Lz) and the number of particles (N)
2) Compile createXYZ: g++ createXYZ.cpp pdbio.cpp xyzio.cpp -o cxyz
3) Run ./cxyz to create the initial coordinate file: Atomscoor.xyz

4) In main.cu change the dimensions of the box (L) and the number of particles (N)
5) In main.cu in the line:
        	readLJPar("LJPar", &lj);
   choose LJPar to simulate phase separation and LJPar_AB to simulate crystallization. 
   These are the parameters in Lennard-Jones potential (U(r) = e[A(sigma/r)^12 + B(sigma/r)^6])
6) Compile the main code: nvcc main.cu dcdio.cpp pdbio.cpp psfio.cpp xyzio.cpp hicio.cpp -o box
7) Run ./box
